did.unittitle: Walt Roycraft photographs
did.abstract: The Walt Roycraft photographs (dated 1990-2005, undated; 1.26 cubic feet; 8 boxes) comprise negatives and photographs taken by Walt Roycraft documenting his career as a commercial photographer primarily in Lexington, Kentucky, during the 1990s and 2000s.

accessrestrict.head: Conditions Governing Access
accessrestrict.p: Collection is open to researchers by appointment

bioghist.head: Biographical note
bioghist.p: Walt Roycraft has been a photographer since 1970. He owns and operates Walt Roycraft Photography, opened in 1982, in Nicholasville, Kentucky. As a commercial photographer, Roycraft photographs the interiors and exteriors of buildings primarily in Central Kentucky.

prefercite.head: Preferred Citation
prefercite.p: 2015av009: [identification of item], Walt Roycraft photographs, 1990-2005, undated, University of Kentucky Libraries, Special Collections Research Center.

scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents
scopecontent.p: The Walt Roycraft photographs (dated 1990-2005, undated; 1.26 cubic feet; 8 boxes) comprise negatives taken by Walt Roycraft documenting his career as a commercial photographer primarily in Lexington, Kentucky, during the 1990s and 2000s. The collection includes negatives depicting the interiors and exteriors of buildings in Kentucky, including buildings in Lexington, Louisville, Covington, Moorehead, and Richmond. The collection documents medical buildings and interiors; schools; banks; university buildings, including the University of Kentucky, Eastern Kentucky University, and Moorehead College; businesses; and courthouses.

userestrict.head: Conditions Governing Use
userestrict.p: The physical and intellectual rights to the materials in this collection are held by the University of Kentucky Special Collections Research Center.
